I"À<p>Rendering a photograph from a light field image is computationally intensive. However it can be greatly sped up using a GPU for parallel processing. <a href="https://github.com/damienfir/lytrogl">LytroGL</a> is a viewer for light field images using OpenGL. This software aims to provide an interactive interface to refocus <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">.lfp</code> images captured with the Lytro.</p>

<p>In previous post, I describe how to use the metadata in the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">.lfp</code> files to correctly decode light field information from a raw 2D image.</p>

